1. *Obećanje* je bilo da ćeš doći u petak. (The *promise* was that you would come on Friday.)
2. Nadam se da ćeš ispunjavati *obećanja* koja daješ. (I hope you will keep the *promises* you make.)
3. Da li si mu dao *obećanje* da ćeš mu pomoći? (Did you give him your *promise* to help him?)
4. Oni su ispunili svoje *obećanje* i donirali novac za dobrotvorne svrhe. (They fulfilled their *promise* and donated money for charity.)
5. Ne možeš stalno davati *obećanja* koja ne možeš da ispuniš. (You can't keep giving *promises* that you can't fulfill.)
6. Sutra će biti održan sastanak o tome kako da se ispuni *obećanje* o boljim uslovima rada. (Tomorrow, there will be a meeting about how to fulfill the *promise* of better working conditions.)
7. *Obećanje* je dug i treba ga ispunjavati. (A *promise* is a debt and should be kept.)
8. Dao sam joj *obećanje* da ću doći po nju u 6 sati. (I gave her my *promise* to pick her up at 6 o'clock.)
9. Bilo je mnogo *obećanja* u predizbornoj kampanji, ali malo toga se ostvarilo. (There were a lot of *promises* made during the election campaign, but little was fulfilled.)
10. Kada datira tvoje *obećanje* da ćeš završiti ovaj projekat? (When does your *promise* to finish this project date back to?)